FOOD POISONING - EGYPT (MANSOURA): REQUEST FOR INFO
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Tue, 13 Oct 1998
From: zowie@telis.org
Source: Nando.net

Hundreds of Egyptian students hospitalized after eating tainted biscuits
----------------------------------------------------------------------
CAIRO, Egypt (October 13, 1998 02:03 a.m. EDT
http://www.nandotimes.com) --
Some 1400 children have been hospitalized in northern Egypt due to
eating
tainted school biscuits, police said.
The children were rushed to hospitals Sunday and treated for food
poisoning
after eating the biscuits in primary,middle and secondary schools in
Darin
village, in the Nile delta province of Mansoura, a police official
said,
speaking on customary condition of anonymity.
The village is 70 miles northeast of Cairo.
Most of the students were discharged, but five remained in intensive
care
units, the official said.
Maj. Gen. Fakreddin Khaled, the governor of Mansoura, ordered police to
detain the distributor of the biscuits pending an investigation.
[We have held this report up, hoping for identification of the cause.
Can anyone give us any further info? - Mod.JW]
..........................jw
